Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveFrance’s President Emmanuel Macron dislikes populism, and has derided Poland and Hungary—countries he believes his rival Marine Le Pen will ally with and facilitate a Frexit if she wins.
But Macron doesn’t mind exhibitionism—if it helps him win a re-election. Or woo voters.
His official photographer released a series of behind-the-scenes pictures ahead of the second round of voting for the France presidential election on Monday
The photos feature silhouettes, some shots of Macron running on the stage and audiences.
One image that has caught the public’s eye has Macron lounging on a mustard yellow sofa. In the candid picture, Macron is wearing a white shirt — unbuttoned to reveal his hairy chest. One of the sleeves is partially rolled up as he casually looks at the camera
